        <stimulus>[Graph showing the growth of trusts: 1895: 40 trusts controlling $1 billion in capital, 1904: 318 trusts controlling $7 billion in capital]</stimulus>
        <prompt>This economic trend most directly motivated which Progressive Era president's actions?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">William McKinley's monetary policies</option>
            <option letter="b">Theodore Roosevelt's trust-busting</option>
            <option letter="c">William Taft's foreign policy</option>
            <option letter="d">Woodrow Wilson's banking reforms</option>
        </options>
        <answer>b</answer>
        <explanation>The rapid growth of trusts prompted Theodore Roosevelt's "trust-busting" campaign, leading to increased enforcement of the Sherman Antitrust Act and regulation of monopolies.</explanation>
    </question>
